title: Longest Common Subsequence
description: A subsequence of a string is a new string generated from the original string with some characters (can be none) deleted without changing the relative order of the remaining characters. A common subsequence of two strings is a subsequence that is common to both strings. In this problem, you are given two strings `text1` and `text2`. Your task is to find the length of their longest common subsequence. If there is no common subsequence, return 0.
input_format: Two lines containing the strings text1 and text2.
output_format: Output a single integer representing the length of the longest common subsequence of `text1` and `text2`.
